definitions.definition: A country consisting of a main island , the island of Tasmania and other smaller islands, located in Oceania ; historically, a collection of former colonies of the British Empire . Official name: Commonwealth of Australia . Capital: Canberra .
A continent consisting of the land on the Australian tectonic plate , i.e. Australia , New Guinea and intervening islands.
examples: He is going to Australia for his honeymoon for 10 days.
